data.name: customSqlQuery1.Sql
data.value: select "OrderDetails"."Quantity", "OrderDetails"."UnitPrice", "OrderDetails"."DefaultPrice", "OrderDetails"."Discount", "OrderDetails"."Increase", "OrderDetails"."TotalCustomer", "OrderDetails"."OrderID", "OrderDetails"."ShipperID", "OrderDetails"."SortShipper", "OrderDetails"."SortProduct", "Products"."ProductName", "Shippers"."ShipperName" from ((("dbo"."OrderDetails" "OrderDetails" inner join "dbo"."Products" "Products" on ("Products"."ProductID" = "OrderDetails"."ProductID")) inner join "dbo"."Shippers" "Shippers" on ("Shippers"."ShipperID" = "OrderDetails"."ShipperID")) inner join "dbo"."Orders" "Orders" on ("Orders"."OrderID" = "OrderDetails"."OrderID")) where ("OrderDetails"."OrderID" = @OrderID) and ("Products"."ProductID" != 10) order by ("OrderDetails"."SortShipper") asc, ("OrderDetails"."SortProduct") asc

data.value: select "OrderDetails"."Quantity", "OrderDetails"."UnitPrice", "OrderDetails"."DefaultPrice", "OrderDetails"."Discount", "OrderDetails"."Increase", "OrderDetails"."TotalCustomer", "OrderDetails"."OrderID", "OrderDetails"."ShipperID", "OrderDetails"."SortShipper", "OrderDetails"."SortProduct", "Products"."ProductName", "Shippers"."ShipperName" from ((("dbo"."OrderDetails" "OrderDetails" inner join "dbo"."Products" "Products" on ("Products"."ProductID" = "OrderDetails"."ProductID")) inner join "dbo"."Shippers" "Shippers" on ("Shippers"."ShipperID" = "OrderDetails"."ShipperID")) inner join "dbo"."Orders" "Orders" on ("Orders"."OrderID" = "OrderDetails"."OrderID")) where ("Products"."ProductID" = 10) order by ("OrderDetails"."SortShipper") asc, ("OrderDetails"."SortProduct") asc

data.name: xrLabel25.Text
data.value:
Do you need a privacy policy if you don’t collect any kind of personal data?
A privacy policy is a legal agreement that discloses the way you gather, use and manage the personal information of your customers and clients.
Personal information can be anything that identifies an individual, including but not limited to name, address, date of birth, marital status, contact information, financial records and credit information.
It is very important that your privacy policy informs users whether their information stays confidential or will be shared with third parties (that you need to run your business, e.g. MailChimp to send email campaigns).
